@startuml
title Car Status Lifecycle (Detailed Version)



== USER BORROWING PROCESS ==

AVAILABLE --> BORROWED : Borrow request approved & rental started
note left of BORROWED
Triggered by:
• Car marked as "in use"
end note

BORROWED --> AVAILABLE : Car returned and inspected
note right of AVAILABLE
Triggered by:
• User returns the car  
• Car becomes available again
end note

== CAR MAINTENANCE PROCESS ==

AVAILABLE --> MAINTENANCE : Sent for service or repair
note right of MAINTENANCE
Triggered by:
• Admin schedules maintenance  
• Automatic flag after inspection failure
end note

MAINTENANCE --> AVAILABLE : Maintenance completed and approved
note right of AVAILABLE
Triggered by:
• Mechanic/admin confirms maintenance done  
• Car passes post-maintenance inspection  
• Car becomes available for new rentals
end note

@enduml
